
- *Methylprednisolone failure in Long COVID integration* ([Chapter 19, 8 new environments (1 warning, 4 hypotheses, 3 speculations); Appendix H, new section with 1 annotated entry; references.bib, 1 new entry; hypothesis-registry.typ, new section with 8 entries; Phase 3 brainstorm: 30 ideas generated across 9 categories]): Integration of negative PoCoVIT trial results demonstrating methylprednisolone ineffectiveness in Long COVID with high adverse event rate. Trial terminated early (96/418 enrolled, 5 serious AEs) with no efficacy vs placebo on any outcome. Phase 3 brainstorm generated 30 creative hypotheses across novel mechanisms, research directions, drug ideas, supplements, non-pharmacological interventions, combinations, math model extensions, cross-disease bridges, and diagnostics. Integrated 8 high-priority ideas: warning environment documenting trial failure; 4 hypotheses (corticosteroid-induced HPA "trust-breaking", viral reactivation via NK suppression, transcriptional reprogramming trap, GR isoform imbalance); 3 speculations (corticosteroids may worsen outcomes, steroid-sparing anti-inflammatory protocol, post-steroid recovery protocol, VNS as steroid alternative). Updated hypothesis registry with 8 entries. Created hypothesis subtree file with 30 nodes. _Motivated by:_ @Adam2024PoCoVIT — PoCoVIT trial terminated early due to adverse events, showing no methylprednisolone benefit in Long COVID; negative result provides cautionary evidence against corticosteroid trials in ME/CFS and spawned extensive hypothesis generation about alternative mechanisms and steroid-avoidant strategies.

