12	*Connective tissue disorders integration* ([Chapter 13, new section with 1 hypothesis environment; Chapter 14a, new section with 1 hypothesis environment; Chapter 14k, new subsection with dysautonomia prevalence data; Appendix H, 10 new annotated entries; references.bib, 10 new entries; hypothesis-registry.typ, 2 new entries]): Integration of connective tissue disorders (CTDs) in ME/CFS, focusing on bidirectional relationship with ME/CFS pathophysiology. Added bidirectional CTD-ME/CFS relationship hypothesis to Chapter 13 (certainty 0.45) with evidence for: (1) CTD predisposition via hypermobility (30-57% in ME/CFS vs 10-15% general population), craniocervical instability, autonomic dysfunction, and mast cell hyperactivity; (2) ME/CFS exacerbation of CTD via ROS-mediated inhibition of prolyl hydroxylases (impairing collagen crosslinking), chronic HIF-1$alpha$ elevation (altering extracellular matrix composition), mast cell activation (MMP-mediated collagen degradation), and basement membrane thickening in capillaries (impairing perfusion). Added HIF-1$alpha$-mediated connective tissue remodeling hypothesis to Chapter 14a (certainty 0.55) linking tendinopathy mechanisms (direct ECM alteration, VEGF-independent pathology, MMP-3-mediated degradation) to ME/CFS connective tissue pathology. Added dysautonomia prevalence data to Chapter 14k: 64% dysautonomia prevalence in chronic musculoskeletal pain (meta-analysis N=1420, RR=2.28 vs controls), POTS comorbidities (31% hypermobility, 36.3% MCAS, 40.9% chronic fatigue), and hEDS/HSD patient experience data (diagnostic delay 19-21 years, 45.6% unemployment). Updated hypothesis registry with 2 new entries. _Motivated by:_ @Wirth2026CTDMECFS — preprint proposing bidirectional CTD-ME/CFS relationship and linking ROS, HIF-1$alpha$, mast cell pathways to connective tissue pathology; @Ganesh2024LongCOVIDHSD — hypermobility prevalence data and Long COVID-HSD shared pathophysiology; @Ramirez-Paesano2023CCI — craniocervical instability producing ME/CFS-like symptoms in EDS; @Moschini2026HIFTendinopathy — HIF-1$alpha$ as driver (not marker) of tendinopathy with direct ECM alteration; @Sahin2012HIFTendon — HIF-1$alpha$/VEGF/MMP-3 cascade reducing biomechanical stability; @Almutairi2026DysautonomiaMSD — dysautonomia meta-analysis in chronic musculoskeletal pain; @Kulin2026POTSGI — POTS GI symptoms and comorbidities meta-analysis; @Berg2026HSDSurvey — hEDS/HSD lived experience survey; @Wilson2026hEDSWearable — hEDS wearable monitoring of autonomic dysfunction; @Eccles2021hypermobility — hypermobility prevalence in ME/CFS/FM clinic population.

